1. Equilibrium condition at $r=0$:
$$f(x^*;0,h)=0\;\implies\;-x^{*3}+h=0\;\implies\;x^{*3}=h\;\implies\;x^*=h^{1/3}.$$

2. Linear stability eigenvalue:
$$\lambda=\frac{df}{dx}\Big|_{x=x^*}
= r -3x^{*2}\Big|_{r=0}
=-3\,x^{*2}
=-3\,(h^{1/3})^2
=-3\,h^{2/3}.$$
Since $h^{2/3}=|h|^{2/3}$, we have $\lambda=-3|h|^{2/3}$.

3. Relaxation time:
$$\tau=\frac{1}{|\lambda|}
=\frac{1}{3\,|h|^{2/3}}
\;\propto\;|h|^{-2/3}.$$

Thus the scaling exponent satisfies $\tau\propto|h|^\alpha$ with
$$\alpha=-\tfrac{2}{3}.$$
